South Africa has recorded 1 641 new coronavirus cases. This brings the total number of cases to 688 532. The country has also recorded 139 new COVID-19 related fatalities, bringing the total number of deaths to 17 547. In a statement, Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says most of the new deaths were recorded in KwaZulu-Natal. “Regrettably, we report 139 more COVID-19 related deaths: “65 from KwaZulu-Natal, 28 from Gauteng, 23 from Eastern Cape, 3 from the Free State, 4 from Limpopo, 7 from the North West, 4 from the Northern Cape and 5 from Western Cape,” says Dr Mkhize. The cumulative number of tests conducted to date is 4 360 105. The number of recoveries now stands at 620 081, this translates to a recovery rate of 90%. As of today, the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 688 532, the total number of deaths is 17 547 and the total number of recoveries is 620 081. pic.twitter.com/yuRpLd8v7g — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) October 9, 2020 